1. If he wins one million dollars, he will buy an expensive car. (If he should win
one million dollars, he will buy an expensive car.)
2. If he won one million dollars today, he would buy an expensive car. (If he
should win one million dollars today, he would buy an expensive car.)
3. If he had won one million dollars at that time, he would have bought an
expensive car.
4. If he had won one million dollars at that time, he would buy an expensive car now.
5. If he had won one million dollars at that time, he would be buying an expensive
car right now.
